{"questionId":"9080837","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The graph shows the effect of relative humidity on the transpiration rate in Chinese privet (<em>Ligustrum sinense</em>).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/5c0c4377c3b0107f38827624e4f130d20f85759c.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The rate of water uptake was measured using the potometer shown in the diagram. The diameter of the capillary tube is 1 mm.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/e1a5e44f5ae690266c4440d9360120425badda1d.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State a variable that needs to be controlled in this experiment.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>temperature<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>atmospheric pressure<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>solar radiation/light<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>wind speed<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>leaf area<br><em><strong>OR&nbsp;</strong></em><br>size of plant</p>\n<p><em>Do not accept humidity.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9080837","referenceCode":"18M.3.HL.TZ2.3b","subjectId":"43-dp-biology-last-assessment-2024","title":"State a variable that needs to be controlled in this experiment.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level","Additional higher level","Topic 9: Plant biology","9.1 Transport in the xylem of plants","Additional higher level","Topic 9: Plant biology"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}